AGI - "NATO plays an essential role in this historical period as regards global crisis scenarios and other situations, such as terrorism, cyber attacks or misinformation. The Mediterranean, a crossroads of cultures, economic and commercial exchanges, is an increasingly fundamental region for global security." &nbsp;<br> This was said by the President of the House, Lorenzo Fontana, opening the meeting of the special group Mediterranean and Middle East of the Parliamentary Assembly of NATO.&nbsp;
<div </div
<br> "Highly important is the diplomatic role of Italy - it has emphasized Fontana -, who has been able to establish profitable relations also outside the West, starting a solid cooperation with the countries of the Arab world and Africa. The positive relations of Italy therefore represent an added value for the entire Alliance, which seeks to build a constructive dialogue with the other actors on the international political scene. In this context, I would like to emphasize the importance of the Parliament's dimension, which is first and foremost the role and essential activity of the House on the intergovernmental side. It is therefore necessary to strengthen the agreement between national parliaments and the NATO Parliamentary Assembly to raise public awareness on the defence of the democratic values of the Alliance and on security priorities. But more generally, parliamentary diplomacy is a turning point for bilateral and multilateral relations. It facilitates dialogue, mutual understanding and sharing common values of freedom, democracy and rule of law with wider margins of manoeuvre than those to be held by government institutions. The parliamentary summit of the leaders of the Allied Parliaments and the Heads of Delegation of the NATO Assembly, which will take place in Washington on 8 and 9 July on the eve of the NATO Summit, bears witness to the crucial importance of the parliamentary dimension and its undoubted added value."
&nbsp;
&nbsp;

