"Italy, which is the seat of the Presidency of the G7>, still maintains - as a firm point of its action both its membership in the European Union and the Atlantic Alliance, as well as multilateralism on the United Nations system; the action of our country is aimed, in all crisis theatres, to the protection of international peace and security in a framework of open and inclusive global collaboration, with a priority strategic attention to the region of the Mediterranean 'allargated' and to the Western Balkans, whose balances are deeply touched by the crisis in Eastern Europe'. &nbsp;
